title: proposal: add Set builtin type
body:
Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

1. What version of Go are you using (`go version`)?
1.6.2

2. What operating system and processor architecture are you using (`go env`)?
Windows amd64

3. What did you do?
Go doesn't provide Set type. I need create  the Set type via map which looks very ugly.
Besides, I have to implement the functions by self.

4. What did you expect to see?
Have one builtin type Set and some more builtin functions like put, intersection and difference
